    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                <name type="place" rend="right">431 Stevens</name>
                <name type="place" rend="right">Camden</name>
                <date when="1876-07-13" rend="right">July 13</date></dateline>
                <salute>Nelly,</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>this is a sad house to-day&#8212;little Walt<ptr target="n0712"/> died last
                evening about &#188; past 8. Partially sick but sudden at last&#8212;suddenly turned
                to water on the brain&#8212;is to be buried to-morrow afternoon at 4&#8212;</p>
            <p>George<ptr target="n0700b"/> and Lou<ptr target="loc.00665_n2"/> are standing it pretty 
                well&#8212;I am miserable&#8212;he knew me so
                well&#8212;we had already such good times&#8212;&#38; I was counting so
                much&#8212;My St. Louis nieces<ptr target="duk.00434_n1b"/> are here&#8212;they 
                are well&#8212;Nelly dear, send me back their photos &#38; 
                Jeff's<ptr target="n4995"/>&#8212;the heat here has been &#38; is
                dreadful&#8212;Love to you&#8212;write&#8212;</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>W W</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
